## Part 3: Add a Design System

This step installs a library of pre-made, good-looking buttons, forms, and menus so you don't have to design everything from scratch.

### Step 3.1 — Initialize the Design System

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

Choose these options when asked:

```text
Template               → Next.js
Base (component style) → Radix
Preset (color theme)   → Nova
```

### Step 3.2 — Install a Starter Set of Components

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button card input textarea label dialog form dropdown-menu avatar badge sheet tabs table alert alert-dialog navigation-menu separator scroll-area skeleton checkbox switch select popover calendar tooltip sonner
```

This downloads ready-made pieces like buttons, tables, and pop-up dialogs directly into your project. You can add more later, any time, by running `npx shadcn@latest add <name>`.

