## Part 10: Publish Your App

### Step 10.1 — Build a Signed App File

Inside Android Studio: **Build → Generate Signed Bundle / APK**

- Choose **APK** if you're just testing.
- Choose **AAB** if you're submitting to the Google Play Store.

*(You can also build without opening Android Studio's interface at all, by running `cd android && ./gradlew assembleDebug` in the terminal — it produces the file at `android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`.)*

### Step 10.2 — Deploy the Website Version

Your website (not the Android app) also needs to be hosted somewhere so people can visit it in a browser. Pick one:

- [Vercel](https://vercel.com) (easiest option for Next.js — one click deploy from GitHub)
- [Netlify](https://netlify.com)
- [Firebase Hosting](https://firebase.google.com/products/hosting)
- [Cloudflare Pages](https://pages.cloudflare.com)

### Step 10.3 — Save Your Work to GitHub

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial project setup"
git push origin main
```

