## Final Config Files (Copy-Paste Reference)

These two files are the most important ones in the whole setup. If something isn't working, check these first.

**`next.config.ts`**

```typescript
import type { NextConfig } from "next";

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  output: "export",
  trailingSlash: true,
  images: {
    unoptimized: true,
  },
};

export default nextConfig;
```

**`capacitor.config.ts`**

```typescript
import type { CapacitorConfig } from '@capacitor/cli';

const config: CapacitorConfig = {
  appId: 'com.example.app',
  appName: 'myapp',
  webDir: 'out'
};

export default config;
```

> Replace `appId` and `appName` with your own app's details. `webDir: 'out'` must match the folder Next.js generates during `npm run build` — if this is wrong, nothing after it will work correctly.

