## Troubleshooting — Common Errors and Fixes

| What you see | What it means | How to fix it |
|---|---|---|
| `The web assets directory (./public) must contain an index.html file` | You skipped building the project, or `webDir` still says `public` | Run `npm run build`, then check `capacitor.config.ts` says `webDir: 'out'` |
| `ENOENT: ...capacitor.plugins.json` | A previous failed attempt left behind a half-finished `android` folder | Run `rm -rf android`, fix the issue above, then run `npx cap add android` again |
| `android platform already exists` | Same as above — leftover folder from a failed attempt | `rm -rf android` then retry `npx cap add android` |
| `Unable to launch Android Studio. Is it installed?` | The command doesn't know where Android Studio is installed | Find the path with `find / -iname "studio.sh" 2>/dev/null`, then type it directly into the command as shown in Step 9.2 |
| Android Studio: *"This step is blocked — Cannot find AGP version"* | The auto-upgrade tool can't read the version format Capacitor uses | Manually edit the version numbers in `android/build.gradle` and `gradle-wrapper.properties` (see Step 9.3), then sync manually |
| Login/session doesn't seem to work with Supabase | The special `proxy.ts` file is missing or misnamed | Make sure the file is named exactly `proxy.ts` and sits at the very top level of your project (not `middleware.ts`, and not inside a folder) |

